title: Alex Pattakos-Prisoners Of Our Thoughts
description:
World-renowned psychiatrist Viktor Frankl's "Man's Search for Meaning" is one of the most important books of modern times. Frankl's personal story of finding a reason to live in the most horrendous of circumstances--Nazi concentration camps--has inspired millions. Now, "Prisoner of Our Thoughts" applies Frankl's philosophy to the workplace, detailing seven principles for increasing your capacity to deal with work challenges, finding meaning in your daily work life, and achieving your highest potential.

   Alex Pattokos, Ph.D., a dedicated student of Frankl's thought, was urged by Frankl himself to create this important audiobook. In it, Pattakos draws on the entire body of Frankl's work illustrating his philosophy through seven easy-to-understand principles.
